args: I never miss a chance to train.
Your movements are more composed\nthan they were before.
Yes, it seems both your body and mind\nhave matured during your time here.
Aw, stop. You'll make me blush.
So not to kick you out the door,\nbut wasn't the plan to go back to\nHinomoto once you were stronger?
Yep. And then I'm going to give Mr. Next\nCandidate for Shogun a good ol' slap on\nthe back!
So how strong are you trying to be?
Hmm. You know, that's a good question.
Stronger than Ieyasu, I guess.\nBut how MUCH stronger...?
Oh man! I'm really sorry, guys.\nI totally spaced there.
Something's clearly been worrying you\nthese past few days, Botan. What is it?
Well, I know I'm stronger, right?\nBut I don't know how MUCH stronger.
My goal before was to defeat Ieyasu,\nbut things are different now.
At first I was doing this to help him,\nbut now I feel like I want to be strong\njust to be strong, if that makes sense.
Somewhere along the way, I think I lost\nsight of my actual goal.
So, like, how strong do you have to be\nbefore you can say ＂Okay, I'm strong now＂?
I don't know the answer to that.
I have many companions here in the\ncastle, and each of them has their\nown kind of strength.
I learn different things from them every\nday, but I'm still searching for my own\nanswer to that question.
Yeah, I guess that's not a question with\na neat little answer, huh?
I mean, should I keep training here\nwithout a specific end goal?
That's exactly what you should do.
Even if you don't have an answer now,\nyou'll eventually find it if you keep\ntraining and learning from all of us.
You'll find what it is you want to be.
Huh. I never thought of it like that.
We've turned the Halidom upside down\nand haven't found even a whiff of her!
It's very unlike her to wander away\nwithout even a word.
Maybe she decided her trainin' was done\nand went back to Hinomoto?
Or perhaps she no longer saw a point\nin training here.
If so, I'm sad we couldn't help her.
Hoo boy, look at the time!\nDidn't realize how late it was.
Wait, were you guys looking for me?\nOh man, I'm sorry!
I was looking for a merchant that was\nheading to Hinomoto, but I struck out.
I wanted them to deliver a letter to\nmy dojo and friends back in Hinomoto.
I pray it was not an ＂expect me soon＂\nsort of notice?
What? No, no! It's not that at all.

See, when I first came here I was just
a huge ball of energy, but things kinda
settled a little once I moved into
your big castle.
That's why I wanted to let everyone back\nhome know that I'm gonna be working\nhard for you from now on.
It was only when you said it to me\nthat I realized it, {player_name}.
I didn't know how strong I should be,\nor even how strong I WAS.
But now I realize it's way better to just\nwork as hard as I can and not worry\nabout all that jazz!
It's like you said: I'll find my answer if\nI just keep working with everyone here.
I'll find the strength I want.
Anyway, all that to say I'm gonna stick\naround for a while if you're cool with it.
Wait, so yer stayin'? Dammit, I can't keep\nyou straight sometimes!
But in the end, we get to keep you here,\nand that's all that matters.
We'll do everything we can to help you\nbecome whatever you want to be, Botan.
Aw, thanks everybody. I can't wait!
